        <mxCell id="ByctPHMSPlSi7kCvrzLa-10" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Proxy Design Pattern&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;b data-index-in-node=&quot;4&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Proxy Design Pattern&lt;/b&gt; is a structural pattern that provides a placeholder, or surrogate, for another object. A proxy controls access to the original object, allowing you to perform actions either &lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;199&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;before&lt;/i&gt; or &lt;i data-index-in-node=&quot;209&quot; data-path-to-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;after&lt;/i&gt; the request reaches the target object.&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
